        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:46AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 246 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Shelby, or 12 miles southwest of Columbus, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Polk
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
